Example Usage: Entering Product Name
Navigation:

The customer visits the product management system website and is presented with the homepage.
View Products:

The customer clicks on the "View Products" button or navigates to the product listings page.
Browsing Products:

The customer scrolls through the list of available products and finds a product they are interested in.
Selecting a Product:

Interested in a particular product, the customer clicks on its title or image to view more details.
Product Details Page:

On the product details page, the customer sees fields to input information such as name, description, price, and stock.
Entering Product Name:

The customer focuses on the "Product Name" input field.
They click or tap on the field, activating it for text input.
Using their keyboard or touchscreen, the customer enters the name of the product they are searching for. For example, "Premium Wireless Headphones."
Submitting Product Name:

After entering the product name, the customer clicks the "Search" button or presses the "Enter" key to submit the query.
Search Results:

The system processes the entered product name and returns relevant search results, displaying matching products that match the entered name.
Selecting a Product from Results:

The customer reviews the search results and clicks on the desired product to view its details further.
